  "body": "After discussion with Alex, we think the proper policy is for dtors to not fail. This is consistent with C++ best practice, which has the same double-failure semantics. BufferedWriter already does this, so this patch modifies TempDir to not fail in the dtor, adding a `close` method for handling errors on destruction.\n",
